# reinguard bridge (Adapter layer)

This file is an **adapter**: it points at the Semantics layer (`.reinguard/`)
and Substrate (`rgd`). Do not duplicate body text from `.reinguard/` here.

## Entry points

- **Substrate config**: [.reinguard/reinguard.yaml](../../.reinguard/reinguard.yaml) — `schema_version`, `default_branch`, `providers` (ADR-0008, ADR-0009).
- **Knowledge catalog**: [.reinguard/knowledge/manifest.json](../../.reinguard/knowledge/manifest.json) — `entries[]` with `id`, `path`, `description`, `triggers` (ADR-0010).
- **Policy catalog** (normative, not in knowledge manifest): [.reinguard/policy/catalog.yaml](../../.reinguard/policy/catalog.yaml) — `entries[]` with `id`, `path`, `description`; bodies live under [.reinguard/policy/](../../.reinguard/policy/).
- **Control catalog**: [.reinguard/control/catalog.yaml](../../.reinguard/control/catalog.yaml) — `entries[]` with `id`, `path`, `type`, `description`; rule files under [.reinguard/control/states/](../../.reinguard/control/states/), [routes/](../../.reinguard/control/routes/), [guards/](../../.reinguard/control/guards/) — consumed by `config.Load` / `rgd config validate`.

## Always-active policy

Follow these policy documents in every interaction:

- [safety--agent-invariants.md](../../.reinguard/policy/safety--agent-invariants.md) — **HARD STOPS (HS-*)**:
  - **HS-CI-MERGE** — green CI before merge; no `--admin`
  - **HS-PR-TEMPLATE** — all PR template sections required
  - **HS-PR-BASE** — PRs target `main` only
  - **HS-LOCAL-VERIFY** — `go test` / `go vet` / `golangci-lint` before push
  - **HS-NO-SKIP** — no skipping verification without documented exception
  - **HS-REVIEW-RESOLVE** — disposition reply before resolving threads
  - **HS-MERGE-CONSENSUS** — no auto-merge while review pending
- [coding--standards.md](../../.reinguard/policy/coding--standards.md) — English artifacts, `gofmt`, `go vet`, ADR/CLI authority

## Knowledge retrieval

- Triage with `entries` in `manifest.json` (or JSON from `rgd knowledge pack` / `rgd context build`).
- Read only the Markdown paths you need.
- Optional filter:

```bash
rgd knowledge pack --query '<keyword>'
```

Full operational context:

```bash
rgd context build
```

## After changing knowledge front matter

Run `rgd knowledge index` and commit `manifest.json`; then `rgd config validate`.

